BBVA, Iberdrola, Inditex, Telecinco: Spain Equity Market Preview

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-03-23T04:00:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-22/bbva-iberdrola-inditex-telecinco-spain-equity-market-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Spanish trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are from the previous close.  Spain ’s IBEX 35 Index rose less than 0.1 percent to
10,576.1.  Spanish stocks:  Banco Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria SA (BBVA)  : Spain’s
second-largest lender said in a filing it completed its purchase
of a 24.89 percent stake in Turkish lender Turkiye Garanti
Bankasi AS. BBVA shares rose 1 percent to 8.94 euros.  Iberdrola SA (IBE)  : The biggest producer of renewable
energy said in a filing it boosted the maximum share buyback to
4.31 percent of its capital before it merges with  Iberdrola
Renovables SA (IBR)  . The companies’ boards also approved
their merger plans. Iberdrola advanced 0.4 percent to 6.05
euros. Iberdrola Renovables dropped 0.3 percent to 3.05 euros.  Inditex SA (ITX)  : The Spanish retailer that owns the
Zara and Massimo Dutti chains is scheduled to report fourth-
quarter earnings. The shares rose 1.1 percent to 54 euros.  Gestevision Telecinco SA (TL5)  (TL5 SM): Mediaset SpA, the
broadcaster of Italian Prime Minister Silvio Berlusconi that
controls Spain’s largest commercial TV station, said 2010 profit
rose 29 percent on higher advertising sales in Italy and Spain.
The board will propose a dividend of 35 cents per share compared
with 22 cents a share last year. Mediaset also forecast an
increase in net income this year. Telecinco shares fell 1.2
percent to 8.54 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in  Madrid  at 
 mbaigorri@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
